  "text": "Decision tree is also a common method used in classi¯cation. 10 C4.5 is a hierarchical data structure using the divide-and-conquer strategy to growing decision trees. [CITATION_1] In decision trees, each decision node using a test function to partition original data D into subsets D 1 ; D 2 ; . . . ; D n . Suppose the set D consists of C numbers of classes and pðD; jÞ denotes the proportion of cases in D that belongs to the jth class. We can de¯ne the information gain by a test T with m outcomes as Eq. (7):",
